175% over the last 10 years,

00:15:08.637 --> 00:15:11.810
and you can contrast
that to our total growth

00:15:11.810 --> 00:15:16.030
that I told you about was 42%
for our entire population.

00:15:16.030 --> 00:15:18.420
So we're really seeing a
disproportionate growth

00:15:18.420 --> 00:15:21.570
in the number of
individuals who have autism.

00:15:21.570 --> 00:15:25.970
And the totals have
changed from 38,558 in 2008

00:15:25.970 --> 00:15:30.970
to now we just hit 106,000
individuals who have autism.

